{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The speech-to-text output preserves speaker labels so that the summary can attribute statements to specific attendees.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Failure boundary is the STT model’s diarization/content quality, not just local wiring. A stubbed transcript with perfect labels would hide real diarization failures (MOCK-HIDE). System was considered but rejected because behavior correctness is about model output content, which is higher than infrastructure-only execution (System vs Agentic). Workflow was considered but rejected because one model decision (STT labeling quality) is sufficient to fail this behavior.","test_description":"Run real meeting audio through the real STT provider and assert transcript speaker labels remain consistently attributable per utterance so downstream attribution can map statements to attendees.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.68,"Workflow":0.07}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Transcript parsing extracts explicit task assignments (assignee + task text) into the summary input structure.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This behavior is local parsing/normalization logic over transcript text; the failure can be caught at a single function/object boundary (MOCK-MISS says Unit floor). No real OS/network/subprocess or model output quality is required.","test_description":"Feed parser fixture transcripts containing explicit assignment phrases and assert emitted summary-input objects include correct assignee and task text pairs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.72,"Integration":0.24,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The live summary output contains at least one action item for every attendee who was assigned a task during the meeting.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on real LLM extraction/completeness of action items from meeting content (LLM-DEP). Deterministic fixtures would always pass and miss model omission failures (deterministic-assertion trap). Workflow was considered but rejected because this behavior can be validated with a fixed transcript and a single summary-generation model decision.","test_description":"Call the real summarization model on transcripts with known per-attendee assignments and assert each assigned attendee appears with at least one action item in live structured output.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.07,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.73,"Workflow":0.13}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Decision extraction logic routes identified decisions into the `decisions` section schema rather than generic narrative fields.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Behavior targets deterministic routing/mapping logic after decisions are already identified. Failure boundary is local schema-routing code, not external infra or model quality. Integration was considered but rejected because no cross-module state handoff is required by the behavior text itself.","test_description":"Given pre-identified decision records, assert routing function places them in `decisions` schema fields and does not emit them into narrative-only fields.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.7,"Integration":0.24,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Key decisions mentioned in the transcript appear in the live summary's `decisions` section, not buried in the narrative.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"This checks whether real summarization/extraction places important decisions in the correct section; correctness depends on model output content quality (LLM-DEP). Mocked outputs would hide failures where the model mentions decisions only narratively. Workflow was considered but rejected because one model summarization decision on a transcript is enough to expose this failure.","test_description":"Use real transcripts with known decisions, invoke the real summarizer, and assert those decisions are present in `decisions` and not only in freeform narrative text.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.74,"Workflow":0.16}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"When the audio file is longer than 60 minutes, the service splits it into segments and processes them sequentially, merging the results into a single coherent summary.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Behavior explicitly requires multi-step sequential agentic processing across segments plus merged final coherence (MULTI-STEP). A single-call Agentic test is insufficient; orchestration/handoff between repeated model steps is the failure boundary. Integration/System were considered but rejected because real model-dependent coherence across chained steps is required.","test_description":"Run a real >60-minute recording through production chunking flow, verify sequential segment processing occurs, and validate final merged summary remains coherent and structurally unified across segment boundaries.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.25,"Workflow":0.6}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"The full pipeline (upload audio, transcribe, summarize, deliver structured output) completes without manual intervention for a real meeting recording.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This is end-to-end with real recording and chained STT→LLM stages; multiple real agentic steps in sequence are intrinsic (MULTI-STEP). System alone is too low because it would miss failures caused by real model outputs breaking downstream stages. Workflow is the minimum boundary to catch real pipeline failures.","test_description":"Execute full production path on a real meeting file (upload, real STT, real summarization, delivery) and assert unattended completion with valid structured output at the endpoint.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.02,"System":0.18,"Agentic":0.25,"Workflow":0.55}}]}
